   <p>To his Excellency <persName ref="cwgk:N00000258">Beriah Magoffin</persName>
<lb/>Govenor of the <orgName ref="cwgk:O001025">commonwealth of Kentucky</orgName></p>
<p>We the undersigned citizens of <placeName ref="cwgk:P00002615">Hopkins County</placeName> who have heretofore Known <persName ref="cwgk:N00011764">Tho<hi rend="sup">s</hi> B Wadlington</persName> who has been convicted by a jury of the country in the county of 
<lb/><placeName ref="cwgk:P00002472">Caldwell</placeName> of the crime of murder would represent to your excellency that we have Known the unfortunate man long and that his character as a gentleman a true hearted and loyal citizen of the commonwealth of Kentucky <hi rend="str"><unclear/></hi>has never been questioned</p>
<p>It is true that we Know nothing of the circumstances of his case but we feel that we do not depart from the duty that we owe to humanity and to the previous character of the accused as a man of peace industry and Sobriety to ask your honor to review his case and to exercise the powers that are confered upon you to Suspend or modify the rules of strict law and to either extend to the accused a full pardon or a commutation of his punishment as justice tempered with mercy in your opinion may require</p>
<p>Yours Respectfully
